cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as transliteration. Additionally, the use of neural sequence-to-sequence models is a common approach in this sub-category. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine translation and software internationalization are important applications of AI. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for the transliteration task. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as transliteration is important for search engines to retrieve relevant results in different languages. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for the transliteration task.
